Commentary: ha! The fielder at long-off, Roy, had moved straighter after that previous shot, and this time he gets a flatter full one on off stump, which he drills flat, with some wristwork to hit it inside-out, to the fielder's left, forces him into a sliding stop
Commentary_short: Hassan Khan to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: full again, driven down to long-off
Commentary_short: Hassan Khan to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length, angling into off stump, punched down the ground to long-on
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, punched to sweeper cover
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, punched to deep point
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: once again, back of a length and just outside off, punched to backward point
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: length ball angling into middle stump from wide of the crease. Stays on the back foot to defend back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: stops on him slightly - similar ball to the previous one, slanting into middle stump. Wants to whip it through midwicket, and is through his shot too early, gets a leading edge that pops up momentarily but falls well short of extra-cover
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: starts with a friendly one on the pads, tucked away to long leg
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, clipped away to the right of midwicket
Commentary_short: Watson to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: length ball slanting away from off stump, opens his bat face to steer it down to third man
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: short slower one outside off, launches himself through the cut too early and the ball bounces loopily into the keeper's gloves
Commentary_short: Watson to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: another slower one, slanted into the pads. Plays the flick too early and misses
Commentary_short: Watson to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: another short one wide of off, but this is the regular-pace ball, and it sits up nicely for Shadab to slap away, in the air, hard and flat over point. Poor way to finish what was otherwise a pretty decent over
Commentary_short: Watson to Shadab Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length, angling across the left-hander, opens his bat face and steers it through point
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: poor ball, back of a length and angling into Shadab's legs, tucked away neatly to the fine leg boundary
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Shadab Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: fullish outside off, drives to cover with left elbow nice and high
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: slower ball close to off stump, stays back and opens his bat face to dab to backward point
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, punched to deep point
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: length ball close to off stump, comes forward, waits, and plays extremely late to drop the ball gently into the off side, but the man at point charges in to deny him the single
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Duminy, no run

Commentary: back of a length, angling into middle stump. Stops on him slightly as he tries to flick and Shadab sends a leading edge rolling into the covers
Commentary_short: Watson to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: fullish on off stump, punched to the left of mid-off
Commentary_short: Watson to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: fullish, angling away from off stump, driven firmly to extra-cover
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, no run

Commentary: length ball on middle and leg, clipped to midwicket
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, no run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, punched to sweeper cover
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: bowled him! Shadab wanted to hang back and steer this one to third man, and ends up playing slightly inside the line. It's just a straight ball angled into the top of off stump, and he plays it with half a bat. He misses, and Watson hits
Commentary_short: Watson to Shadab Khan, OUT

Commentary: back of a length, neither short nor wide enough to cut, sneaks below his bat
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Duminy, no run

Commentary: slower ball on the pads, pitching outside leg, doesn't quite pick it and misses the flick
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Duminy, no run

Commentary: fullish on middle stump, clipped to the right of the diving midwicket fielder, towards long-on
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: shot! What a way to start. Not too bad a ball, fullish on middle and off, and he makes himself room and flays it away, a powerful drive to the right of the diving extra-cover fielder
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Hussain Talat, FOUR runs

Commentary: fullish again, slanting away from off stump. Doesn't quite come on, keeps a bit low as well, and he overbalances while driving and can't connect
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: slower length ball on middle stump. Stays slightly leg-side of the ball to squeeze it towards backward point
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: back of a length on off stump, punched to deep point
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, back of a length and angling away from off stump. Looks to make a bit of room and dab to third man, can't connect
Commentary_short: Watson to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: fullish on middle and off, eases a drive towards mid-off and starts running as he plays the shot
Commentary_short: Watson to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: short one down the leg side, and Duminy misses out on a scoring opportunity. Looks to pull, only manages a bit of glove on it and it bounces down towards the keeper
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, no run

Commentary: down the track now to the off-stump ball, slices it away in the air, on the bounce, to the right of the sweeper on the cover boundary. Anwar Ali misfields but quickly makes amends
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, 2 runs

Commentary: length ball on middle stump, whipped into the on side, to the right of midwicket
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: full on the pads, and that could be a psychologically deflating hit for Quetta. Flicks it away, high and handsome, waaay beyond the square leg boundary and over the roof, to bring up a beautifully controlled half-century
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Duminy, SIX runs

Commentary: short, angling away from off stump and providing lots of width, slashed hard but too close to backward point to get any runs for it
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Duminy, no run

Commentary: slower length ball wide of off, opens his bat face to stab towards backward point
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Duminy, no run

Commentary: down the track. Anwar sees him coming and fires it wide of off stump. Reaches out to squeeze a single into the covers
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle and leg, and he makes himself lots of room and extends his arms through a big drive that carries all the way over the long-off boundary
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Hussain Talat, SIX runs

Commentary: length ball on off stump, makes room again and slaps it to the left of sweeper cover
Commentary_short: Anwar Ali to Hussain Talat, 2 runs

Commentary: short on off stump, pulled along the ground to the right of deep square leg
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball a long way down the leg side. Perhaps a sign of Watson's struggle with the dew. He saw Talat make a premeditated move across his stumps, and may have wanted to target leg stump, but ended up missing by a long way
Commentary_short: Watson to Hussain Talat, 1 wide

Commentary: bang! That is another huge hit. Again, as he does so often, he makes himself swinging room by moving towards the leg side, and a middle-stump ball is whipped way over the midwicket boundary
Commentary_short: Watson to Hussain Talat, SIX runs

Commentary: fires in a wide yorker, reaches out to try and stab it towards point, and misses. The umpire reckons this is wide enough to be a wide - it was pretty tight with the tramline
Commentary_short: Watson to Hussain Talat, 1 wide

Commentary: and again. Another wide yorker ends up sliding too wide. This one's an easier decision for the umpire to make
Commentary_short: Watson to Hussain Talat, 1 wide

Commentary: shortish on off stump, rises to his toes and dabs gently to the right of backward point
Commentary_short: Watson to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: length ball on middle stump, makes a bit of room to enable a pushed single into the covers
Commentary_short: Watson to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, and Talat meets that with a free, whippy swing of his bat to drill it to the left of long-on
Commentary_short: Watson to Hussain Talat, FOUR runs

Commentary: full and wide, carved hard, along the ground to deep point
Commentary_short: Watson to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: shortish slower one outside off. Talat goes for the big swat over midwicket and misses
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: slower bouncer wide of off, Talat slashes and misses
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: yorker on off stump, jabbed to mid-off
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: another bouncer, over off stump, Talat ducks and lets it pass through to the keeper. Given wide on height
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Hussain Talat, 1 wide

Commentary: shortish outside off, steered down to third man
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: short ball close to off stump, right in his slot to pull, and he ends up pulling it in the air, straight to the man at deep midwicket. A wicket against the run of play for Quetta
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Duminy, OUT
Dismissal_text: JP Duminy c Hassan Khan b Rahat Ali 54 (47b 4x4 2x6) SR: 114.89

Commentary: back of a length close to off stump, steered to the right of third man
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length, slanting across to off stump, lets it come on and guides it to third man
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length, angling into leg stump - saw Talat looking to make himself room and followed him. Jabbed gently into the covers for one
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: length ball slanting across to a sixth-stump line. Takes a big step back into his own crease and slogs across the line, only manages a bottom edge down to fine leg
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off. Goes for an angled-bat jab and ends up getting an inside-edge to short fine leg
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: and he serves one up right in his slot. Full, but not full enough to deny him elevation, and angling into off stump. Clears his front leg and swings cleanly through the line to clear the man at long-on
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Asif Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: digs this in short and angles it across the right-hander. Extra bounce forces him off his feet as he tries to slash over point. Ends up hitting the high part of the bat and looping over the covers. Falls safely beyond the inner ring, though
Commentary_short: Mir Hamza to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: digs in a bouncer, right at Asif's left shoulder, and he's late on the pull. Goes high in the air, but falls to ground beyond square leg, beyond the reach of Pietersen turning around and chasing back
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Asif Ali, 2 runs

Commentary: bang, Asif finishes it in style. Full, on leg stump, and he clears his front leg and sends another sweetly timed lofted hit soaring waaaaay over long-on
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Asif Ali, SIX runs
